main event: A weather balloon was observed by witnesses at the Sergeant Bluff, Iowa airport on July 31, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as moving slowly, stopping and starting, and drifting to the north.
The witnesses were located at the Sergeant Bluff, Iowa airport.
A weather balloon was launched at 0600Z by the local weather bureau and observed by the witnesses.
The object was concluded to be a weather balloon.
The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes.
witnesses: Witnesses at the Sergeant Bluff, Iowa airport
